caption.paragraph:
Fig. 6. –

Croton enigmaticus
P.E. Berry & B.W. van Ee. 
A.
Climbing

habit, here together with a climbing bamboo; 
B.
Adventitious roots emerging from the stems; 
C.
Typical trichotomous branching; 
D.
Leaves; 
E.
Close-up of the densely hirsute newly emergent leaves. Note the falcate stipules and stipitate acropetiolar glands; 
F.
Inflorescence with the pedicels of the staminate flowers perpendicular to the axis of the rachis; 
G.
Pistillate flower. Note the somewhat unequal, foliaceous sepals and thrice bifurcating stigmas; 
H.
Inflorescence showing an immature fruit, foliaceous bracts along the rachis, and staminate pedicels of varying lengths.

